Package neureka.backend.api.algorithms.fun

Interface ADAgentSupplier

All Known Subinterfaces:
Algorithm<C>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractBaseAlgorithm, AbstractFunctionalAlgorithm, Activation, Broadcast, Convolution, FallbackAlgorithm, FunAlgorithm, Operator, Scalarization
public interface ADAgentSupplier
Implementations of this functional interface ought to return a new instance of the ADAgent class responsible for performing automatic differentiation both for forward and backward mode differentiation.
Therefore an ADAgent exposes 2 different procedures.
One is the forward mode differentiation, and the other one
is the backward mode differentiation which is more commonly known as back-propagation...
Besides that it may also contain context information used
to perform said procedures.

  • Method Details

    • supplyADAgentFor

      ADAgent supplyADAgentFor​(Function function, ExecutionCall<? extends Device<?>> call, boolean forward)
      This method ought to return a new instance if the ADAgent class responsible for performing automatic differentiation both for forward and backward mode differentiation.
      Therefore an ADAgent exposes 2 different procedures.
      One is the forward mode differentiation, and the other one
      is the backward mode differentiation which is more commonly known as back-propagation...
      Besides that it may also contain context information used
      to perform said procedures.
      Parameters:
      function - The function from where the request for auto differentiation originates.
      call - The execution call of the current execution which requires auto differentiation support.
      forward - The truth value determining the type of differentiation that should be performed.
      Returns:
      The resulting ADAgent.
